article.headline: Bradley 77, Tennessee Tech 62
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Patrick O'Bryant scored 19 points on 8-of-16 shooting and four Bradley players scored in double figures Saturday to lead the Braves in a 77-62 win over Tennessee Tech. O'Bryant also grabbed 16 rebounds and had nine blocks for Bradley (16-9). The Braves trailed 39-35 at halftime but took advantage of Tennessee Tech's poor second-half shooting by outscoring the Golden Eagles 42-23 after intermission. Lawrence Wright came off the bench to score 16 points on 7-of-14 shooting. Marcellus Sommerville and Daniel Ruffin added 14 and 12, respectively. Amadi McKenzie scored 16 points with seven rebounds to lead Tennessee Tech (17-11). But the Golden Eagles went cold in the second half, connecting on only 29 percent of their field goal attempts compared to Bradley's 52 percent pace. Belton Rivers scored 15 points, and Keyon Boyd added 11 in the loss.
